In this article, President Donald Trump proclaims November 18 to November 24, 2018, as National Family Week. He highlights the importance of families and their contributions to society, emphasizing their role in providing love, support, and values. The article mentions various initiatives and policies implemented by the Trump administration to support families, such as tax cuts, job creation, and family-friendly policies. It also addresses the ongoing issue of drug addiction, particularly the opioid epidemic, and the administration's efforts to combat it. The article concludes by encouraging communities, churches, and individuals to observe National Family Week with appropriate ceremonies and activities.